article.headline: Vermont 65, Hartford 63
article.story: WEST HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Mike Trimboli had 19 points and six assists and Vermont hit 4-of-5 free throws in the final 23 seconds in a 65-63 win over Hartford Thursday night. Vermont (7-7, 3-1 America East) also got 13 points and seven boards from Martin Klimes and nine points and 10 rebounds from Ryan Schneider. Kenny Adeleke had game highs of 20 points and 14 rebounds for Hartford (5-9, 1-3), his seventh-straight double-double and 11th of the season. Adeleke set the school record for the most consecutive double-doubles in the Division I era, passing Vin Baker. He also pulled down his 1,000th career rebound. Aaron Cook added 18 points and eight rebounds for the Hawks. The game was close throughout. Hartford led 23-17 with 3:34 to go in the first half, but the Catamounts closed out the frame with a 13-4 run to take a 30-27 lead at the break. Hartford pulled to within 59-56 when Cook scored with 1:19 remaining in the game, but Klimes converted a layup to push the lead back to five. The Catamounts hit their free throws down the stretch, and Hartford's Paris Carter hit a 3-pointer before the final buzzer.
